compress.info:
Reduce the file size of your PDF.
The level of optimization to apply to the PDF file.  
Higher values indicate greater compression but may reduce quality. 

1-3 PDF compression;
4-6 lite image compression;
7-9 intense image compression Will dramatically reduce image quality.

word.info:
Choose a Word document format based on your needs.

docx: Modern and widely supported;
doc: Legacy format for older systems;
odt: Open format for LibreOffice and similar tools.

ppt.info:
Choose a presentation format based on software compatibility.

pptx: Modern PowerPoint format, widely used;
ppt: Older format for legacy systems;
odp: Open format for LibreOffice Impress.

text.info:
Choose a text format based on content needs.

txt: Plain text for simple notes or code;
rtf: Rich text with basic formatting like bold and italics.
